title: Subservience
overview: With his wife in the hospital, a struggling father purchases a domestic AI to help simplify his home. But as the lifelike robot grows attached to her new owner, boundaries are crossed. Soon she becomes determined to eliminate what she perceives as the true threat to his happiness: his family.

title: Little
overview: HD. When a bullying boss wakes up one morning back in her 13-year-old body, she learns some valuable life lessons.

title: Run All Night
overview: In this intense crime drama, action icon Liam Neeson reteams with the director of Unknown and Non-Stop as a Brooklyn mobster and prolific hit man who must choose between the crime family he serves and the real family he abandoned long ago, when his estranged son becomes a target.

title: Faster
overview: Action star Dwayne Johnson stars as Driver, now a free man after a decade in prison, focused on hunting down the people responsible for the brutal killing of his brother. But fast on his mission are two men who will do anything to stop him.

title: Midway
overview: Based on real events, this is the story of the leaders and soldiers who used their instincts, fortitude and bravery to overcome the odds in the Battle of Midway between the US Navy and the Imperial Japanese Navy, a pivotal turning point in WWII.

title: Transformers
overview: Teenage nerd Shia LaBeouf finds himself at the center of a centuries-old war between two races of transformable alien robots.

title: We're the Millers
overview: In debt to his supplier, a small-time suburban pot dealer travels to Mexico with a fake family to smuggle a large shipment of weed to the U.S.

title: The Ultimatum: Marry or Move On
overview: Get hitched or call it quits? Couples put their love to the test — while shacking up with other potential matches — in a provocative reality series.
